T","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: regional variant of   Bouvier   ‘herdsman’. This surname is also found in Haiti. Compare   Bouyea   and   Boyea  .","Altered form of German   Bayer   or   Beyer  .","German: habitational name for someone from Boye (near Celle-Hanover)."],"variants":[{"name":"Bouvier","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Laurier, Pascal, Adrien, Armand, Christophe, Constant, Dominique, Edouard, Jean Pierre, Jean-Paul, Lucien, Marcel.","French: occupational name for a herdsman, Old French <i>bouvier</i> (from Late Latin <i>bovarius</i>, a derivative of <i>bos</i>, genitive <i>bovis</i> ‘ox’). Compare   Bouvia   and   Bovia  ."]},{"name":"Bouyea","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand.","Americanized form of French   Boyer  ."]},{"name":"Boyea","meanings":["Americanized form of French   Boyer  ."]}]},{"name":"Dianna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Name borne in Roman mythology by the goddess of the moon and of hunting, equivalent to the Greek Artemis. In mythology she is characterized as both beautiful and chaste. Her name is of ancient and uncertain derivation. It probably contains a first element that is also found in the name of the Greek god <i>Dionysos</i> (  see  Dennis  ) and the Latin name of the supreme god <i>Jupiter</i>. It was adopted in Britain during the Tudor period as a learned name, a borrowing from Latin influenced by the French form   Diane .  Although it was much used by Elizabethan poets celebrating the virgin goddess and alluding to the Virgin Queen, it was not particularly popular as a given name until the end of the 19th century. In earlier centuries some clergymen were reluctant to baptize girls with this pagan name, mindful of the riots against St Paul stirred up by worshippers of Diana of the Ephesians (Acts 19:24–41). In the late 20th century, its popularity received a boost because of its association with the late  Diana , Princess of Wales (  1961–97 ), who was renowned for her beauty, glamour, and compassion."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Dianna Boyer was born as the daughter of William Bowyer and Francis Cecil. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Charles Philip Jennens."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1661–Female":"1661–Surnud","1669–Male":"1669–Surnud","1674–1723":"1674–1723","1684–1720":"1684–1720","1688–1720":"1688–1720","–1640":"–1640","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1481–1544":"1481–1544","1723":"1723","ABT 1481":"umbes 1481","1688":"1688","1544":"1544","1720":"1720","1674":"1674","1640":"1640","1684":"1684","1661":"1661","1481":"1481","1669":"1669","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1661–Female":"1661–Kuollut","1669–Male":"1669–Kuollut","1674–1723":"1674–1723","1684–1720":"1684–1720","1688–1720":"1688–1720","–1640":"–1640","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1481–1544":"1481–1544","1723":"1723","ABT 1481":"noin 1481","1688":"1688","1544":"1544","1720":"1720","1674":"1674","1640":"1640","1684":"1684","1661":"1661","1481":"1481","1669":"1669","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1661–Female":"1661–Décédée","1669–Male":"1669–Décédé","1674–1723":"1674–1723","1684–1720":"1684–1720","1688–1720":"1688–1720","–1640":"–1640","–Female":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1481–1544":"1481–1544","1723":"1723","ABT 1481":"environ 1481","1688":"1688","1544":"1544","1720":"1720","1674":"1674","1640":"1640","1684":"1684","1661":"1661","1481":"1481","1669":"1669","Dudleston, Shropshire, England":"Dudleston, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Dianna Boyer est née, fille de William Bowyer et Francis Cecil. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils et 1 fille avec Charles Philip Jennens."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1661–Female":"1661–Verstorben","1669–Male